Vancouver has become one of the most design-forward cities in North America. In 2026, luxury interiors are defined by restraint, texture, and a stronger relationship with natural materials.

## Sculptural Minimalism

Less, but better. Luxury spaces are moving toward cleaner compositions with stronger materials and fewer objects.

## Biophilic Luxury

Natural textures, stone, moss, wood, and soft light are shaping high-end interiors across Vancouver and West Vancouver.

## Heritage Craft

Handmade finishes and artisanal surfaces are becoming a defining mark of premium homes.

## Chromatic Depth

Deep greens, rich neutrals, and moody, elegant palettes are returning.

## The Considered Home

Luxury today is not only visual. It is experiential.
